cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.NA, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper presents distributed algorithms for computing graph distances in the Congested Clique model. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes algorithms for computing all-pairs-shortest-paths, girth, and cycle detection. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper gives lower bounds for matrix multiplication and APSP in the Congested Clique Broadcast model. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses fast matrix multiplication algorithms. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also a less likely category, but the paper does mention the computation of the graph diameter, which is a concept relevant to game theory.
